thought he could enter a house to avoid the horse.
jie të í begetsá jie köũ jũ jãrga estee yiga kabayö yiga este jie gugẽ-wã jula nã

jie (_) (extra) jeskaranã estee (_) nãmã keyege katerinã

Jeska (_) (_) jie suaná-wã tã'ĩ porke nã kenã'nara je të jie kete-mĩ-wã

Jie suaná-ka tã'ĩ begetsá-ite-nã í köũ

So he came out again, and suddely saw a dog/a tiger sleeping.
(_) Jeska í desãũ-nẽ etaba_gicha nẽ ra sũã'-ite-ra-nã estee (_) jueta jueta chichi/ (_) nãmã blali köpö
As he was figuring out how to go out, there came a dog that started to bark at him.
Jie të begetsá desãũ-nẽ-ra-nã jueta chichi dajũ (m) anã' köũ
He did not want the dog to bark because it could awake the tiger and the tiger could devour him.
Jie ka í kianẽ chichi ãr porke (m) chichi nãmã shkiwãka je të jie kete-mĩ-wã

Je kueinganã í klö yasã' jushebega (m) Chichi chichi të í klö bö sigá
He told her to open the door.
The lady fell down at once all scared.
Pemina janã-mĩ jegweta í mẽletenã'-wã je inga
in that moment the tiger stood up and he pretended to be quiet;

ñerö jueta pekaga/ pemina jẽk kaga-te jũkö yáu-mĩ ĩã ra nã
and thought that the tiger was not going to hurt him,
begetsá-ite-ra-nã nãmã ka wã jirö wanẽ ĩã

away he ran and got on to something;
desãũ tu-lë je je bötsáka estee (_) siwã' inga
